q_r2 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(df[['y','z']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
q_r3 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(df[['x','y']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
pval=max(q_r1.chi2_pvalue,q_r2.chi2_pvalue,q_r3.chi2_pvalue)
if pval<0.05:
    print('The p-value is << 0.05, the underlying process is NOT randomly distributed.')
    print('Chi2 P-Value:',pval) # analytical pvalue
else:
    print('The p-value is > 0.05, the underlying process is randomly distributed.')
    print('Chi2 P-Value:',pval) # analytical pvalue
q_r1.plot(title=f'UMa \n Chi^2 = {q_r1.chi2_pvalue:.2e}')
q_r2.plot(title=f'UMa \n Chi^2 = {q_r2.chi2_pvalue:.2e}')

from scipy.stats import qmc
# Assume df has one row representing the center coordinate:
center = toi7032.loc[toi7032.index[0], ['u', 'v', 'w']].values
# Define lower and upper bounds for each coordinate:
value=20 
lb = center - value
ub = center + value
# Choose n points along each axis to get n^3 points
threshold=5
n = int(value/threshold)+1
u_vals = np.linspace(lb[0], ub[0], n)
v_vals = np.linspace(lb[1], ub[1], n)
w_vals = np.linspace(lb[2], ub[2], n)
toi7032_num_within_threshold=full[full['toi7032_velocity_diff']<threshold].GaiaID.count()

# Create the grid
U, V, W = np.meshgrid(u_vals, v_vals, w_vals, indexing='ij')
dd = pd.DataFrame({'u': U.flatten(), 'v': V.flatten(), 'w': W.flatten()})

plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))
plt.hist2d(full.u,full.v,bins=1000)
plt.colorbar(cmap=cm.hot,label='Number of Stars')
plt.scatter(toi7032.u,toi7032.v,marker='x',zorder=10,color='red')

distances=[]
tots=[]
for i in range(0,len(dd)):
    distance=np.sqrt((toi7032['u'].values[0] - dd.u[i])**2 + 
                            (toi7032['v'].values[0] - dd.v[i])**2 + 
                            (toi7032['w'].values[0] - dd.w[i])**2)
    tmp = full[np.sqrt((full['u'] - dd.u[i])**2 + 
                            (full['v'] - dd.v[i])**2 + 
                            (full['w'] - dd.w[i])**2)<threshold]
    tmp['velocity_diff'] = np.sqrt((tmp['u'] - dd['u'][i])**2 + 
                            (tmp['v'] - dd['v'][i])**2 + 
                            (tmp['w'] - dd['w'][i])**2)
    if len(tmp)<1:
        distances.append(np.nan)
        tots.append(np.nan)
    if len(tmp)==1:
        tots.append(1.0)
        distances.append(distance)
    if len(tmp)>1:
        q_r1 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['x','z']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
        q_r2 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['y','z']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
        q_r3 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['x','y']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
        pval=max(q_r1.chi2_pvalue,q_r2.chi2_pvalue,q_r3.chi2_pvalue)
        if (distance>threshold*1.75) and (pval>0.05):
            tots.append(tmp.GaiaID.count())
            distances.append(distance)
            #print(f"Looks like no structure within {len(tmp)} targets")
            #print(f"Velocity dispersion of targets within {threshold} km/s: {round(np.std(tmp['velocity_diff']),5)} km/s")
        else:
            #print(f"Looks like structure within {len(tmp)} targets")
            #print(f"Velocity dispersion of targets within {threshold} km/s: {round(np.std(tmp['velocity_diff']),5)} km/s")
            distances.append(np.nan)
            tots.append(np.nan)
    plt.scatter(tmp.u,tmp.v,alpha=0.1,facecolors='none', lw=0.5,edgecolors='black')
plt.xlim(toi7032.u.values[0]-20,toi7032.u.values[0]+20)
plt.ylim(toi7032.v.values[0]-20,toi7032.v.values[0]+20)
plt.xlabel('U')
plt.ylabel('V')

threshold=5
values=[10,15,20,25,30]
nansfive=[]
for v in range(0,len(values)):
    value=values[v]
    lb = center - value
    ub = center + value
    # Choose n points along each axis to get n^3 points
    n = int(value/threshold)
    u_vals = np.linspace(lb[0], ub[0], n)
    v_vals = np.linspace(lb[1], ub[1], n)
    w_vals = np.linspace(lb[2], ub[2], n)
    # Create the grid
    U, V, W = np.meshgrid(u_vals, v_vals, w_vals, indexing='ij')
    dd = pd.DataFrame({'u': U.flatten(), 'v': V.flatten(), 'w': W.flatten()})
    tots_fivekms=[]
    distances=[]
    for i in range(0,len(dd)):
        distance=np.sqrt((toi7032['u'].values[0] - dd.u[i])**2 + 
                                (toi7032['v'].values[0] - dd.v[i])**2 + 
                                (toi7032['w'].values[0] - dd.w[i])**2)
        tmp = full[np.sqrt((full['u'] - dd.u[i])**2 + 
                                (full['v'] - dd.v[i])**2 + 
                                (full['w'] - dd.w[i])**2)<threshold]
        if len(tmp)<1:
            distances.append(np.nan)
            tots_fivekms.append(np.nan)
        else:
            q_r1 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['x','z']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
            q_r2 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['y','z']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
            q_r3 = qs.QStatistic(PointPattern(tmp[['x','y']]),shape= "hexagon",lh = 5)
            pval=max(q_r1.chi2_pvalue,q_r2.chi2_pvalue,q_r3.chi2_pvalue)
            if (distance>1.75*threshold) and (pval>0.05):
                tots_fivekms.append(tmp.GaiaID.count())
                distances.append(distance)
            else:
                distances.append(np.nan)
                tots_fivekms.append(np.nan)
    nansfive.append(np.nanmedian(tots_fivekms))
distancesfivekms=distances

from scipy.optimize import curve_fit
plt.scatter([6,9,12,18,21,24,27,30],nansthree/full[full['toi7032_velocity_diff']<3].GaiaID.count(),label='3 km/s')
plt.scatter([10,15,20,25,30],nansfive/full[full['toi7032_velocity_diff']<5].GaiaID.count(),label='5 km/s')

def quadratic_model(x, a, b, c):
    return a * x**2 + b * x + c

# Fit the model to the data.
popt, pcov = curve_fit(quadratic_model, [6,9,12,18,21,24,27,30],nansthree/full[full['toi7032_velocity_diff']<3].GaiaID.count())
popt2, pcov2 = curve_fit(quadratic_model, [10,15,20,25,30],nansfive/full[full['toi7032_velocity_diff']<5].GaiaID.count())

# popt contains the best-fit parameters [a, b, c]
print("Fitted parameters:", popt)

# Generate x values for plotting the fitted function.
x_fit = np.linspace(5,30, 30)
y_fit = quadratic_model(x_fit, *popt)
y_fit2 = quadratic_model(x_fit, *popt2)
plt.plot(x_fit,y_fit,color='blue')
plt.plot(x_fit,y_fit2,color='orange')
plt.legend(frameon=True)
plt.ylabel('False Occurrence Rate')
plt.xlabel('Maximum Distance from Velocity Centroid (km/s)')
plt.grid(alpha=0.5)

Fitted parameters: [-0.0006004   0.01180684  0.29216486]
